Yaya Toure has given a signed shirt to a five-year-old girl, who was unfortunately struck in the face by one of his off target shots, in Manchester City's 2-2 draw with QPR.

Chloe Power, who has been a QPR season ticket holder for two years, was hit in the face as the ball went out of play.

The City midfielder wrote on the shirt 'sorry'. QPR also offered a signed shirt to the young girl.

